{
  "texts": [
    "These results demonstrate that the attention mechanism learns to prioritize spatially proximate inputs, even under varying levels of spatial sparsity.",
    "Attention visualization in the physical space We visualize the final attention weights in physical space in fig. 30.",
    "For a selected timestep of a given trajectory, we choose a set of spatial tokens (left panel) and display their corresponding attention scores across the physical domain (middle panel).",
    "The resulting patterns clearly demonstrate that the cross-attention mechanism, guided by the geometryaware bias, preserves locality by assigning high attention weights to nearby regions-effectively focusing on spatially relevant information.",
    "Selected tokens Local attention scores Physical field Figure 30: Attention scores on the vorticity dataset, on spatially selected tokens (left) at a given timestep (t = 15)."
  ]
}